name: Deadlift
description: The deadlift is a weight training exercise in which a loaded barbell or bar is lifted off the ground to the level of the hips, then lowered back to the ground.

name: Squat
description: The squat is a strength exercise in which the trainee lowers their hips from a standing position and then stands back up.

name: Bench Press
description: The bench press is an upper-body weight training exercise in which the trainee presses a weight upwards while lying on a weight training bench.

name: Pull-up
description: A pull-up is an upper-body strength exercise. The pull-up is performed with a palms-forward position.

name: Push-up
description: A push-up is a common calisthenics exercise that targets the muscles of the chest, shoulders, and triceps.

name: Leg Press
description: The leg press is a weight training exercise in which the individual pushes a weight or resistance away from them using their legs.

name: Barbell Row
description: The barbell row is a compound exercise that targets multiple muscles in the back, including the lats, rhomboids, and traps.

name: Lunges
description: Lunges are a single-leg bodyweight exercise that works your hips, glutes, quads, hamstrings, and core and improves balance and stability.

name: Dumbbell Flyes
description: Dumbbell flyes are a strength exercise that target the chest and shoulder muscles.

name: Romanian Deadlift
description: The Romanian deadlift is a variation of the conventional deadlift that targets the hamstrings, glutes, and lower back.

name: Lat Pulldown
description: The lat pulldown is a compound exercise that targets the latissimus dorsi muscle and other muscles of the back and arms.

name: Step-ups
description: Step-ups are a lower-body exercise that targets the quadriceps, hamstrings, glutes, and calves.

name: Chest Press Machine
description: The chest press machine is a weight training exercise that primarily targets the pectoral muscles.

name: Seated Cable Row
description: The seated cable row is a compound exercise that targets the back muscles, including the latissimus dorsi and rhomboids.

name: Leg Curl
description: The leg curl is a resistance exercise that targets the hamstrings and to a lesser extent, the glutes.

name: Dumbbell Bench Press
description: The dumbbell bench press is a variation of the bench press that uses dumbbells instead of a barbell.

name: Good Mornings
description: Good mornings are a compound exercise that targets the lower back, hamstrings, and glutes.

name: Chin-up
description: The chin-up is a strength training exercise. People frequently do this exercise with the intention of strengthening muscles such as the latissimus dorsi and biceps.

name: Hack Squat
description: The hack squat is a machine-based exercise that targets the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes.

name: Chest Fly Machine
description: The chest fly machine is a resistance training machine used to strengthen the pectoralis major muscles of the chest.
